From David Wood Subject Re A KIND and LOVING God Malcolm Lee writes These laws written for the Israelites God's chosen people whom God had expressly set apart from the rest of the The Israelites were a direct witness to God's To disobey God after KNOWing that God is real would be an outright denial of God and therefore immediately Remember these laws were written for a different time and applied only to God's chosen But Jesus has changed all of We are living in the age of Sin is no longer immediately punishable by There is repentance and there is salvation through our Lord Jesus And not just for a few chosen Salvation is available to everyone Jew and Gentile Sorry if this is late for the thread I thought God was supposed to be constant and never How do you reconcile this common Christian view with the paragraph above Also while we're at it How do you reconcile A KIND and LOVING God with the Judeo Christian view that sin was at one time immediately punishable by death Was killing people for sinning God's way of showing KINDness and LOVE Is the fact the He no longer does this an admission on His part of having made a mistake Now that we are living in the age of grace does this mean that for our sins God now damns us to eternal hell after we die rather than killing us immediately If so is this eternal damnation an example of A KIND and LOVING God Just Dave Wood